      "title": "Isolate the kelvin part",
      "content": "Subtract $10$, then multiply both sides by $\\frac{5}{9}$.<br/>$$430.65=\\frac{9(v-273.15)}{5}$$<br/>$$\\frac{5(430.65)}{9}=v-273.15$$<br/>$$239.25=v-273.15$$"
    },
